{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17608137","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17608137"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:29:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:29:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15984"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15984","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15984"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8675"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73459"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8675","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8675"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15984"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58928"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"8592"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20765"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20767"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73459","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73459"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring early placental development, the trophoblast differentiates into cytotrophoblast and syncytiotrophoblast layers. The syncytiotrophoblast is the invasive outer layer that establishes initial contact with maternal tissues.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes trophoblastic lacunae?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Spaces filled with maternal blood in the syncytiotrophoblast","Fluid-filled cavities within cytotrophoblast cells","Channels connecting adjacent placental villi","Spaces between maternal decidual cells","Cavities containing fetal blood vessels"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring early placental development, \u003Cstrong\u003Espaces filled with maternal blood in the syncytiotrophoblast\u003C/strong\u003E form as trophoblastic lacunae. These spaces later join together to form the intervillous space of the mature placenta where maternal-fetal exchange occurs.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFluid-filled cavities within cytotrophoblast cells\u003C/strong\u003E - The cytotrophoblast consists of individual cells with distinct cell membranes and does not contain significant fluid spaces\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChannels connecting adjacent placental villi\u003C/strong\u003E - While the mature placenta has intervillous spaces, these develop later from the coalescence of lacunae\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESpaces between maternal decidual cells\u003C/strong\u003E - These are normal intercellular spaces in the maternal endometrium, not specialised structures in the trophoblast\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECavities containing fetal blood vessels\u003C/strong\u003E - Fetal vessels develop within the chorionic villi, not within the trophoblastic lacunae\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe formation of trophoblastic lacunae is essential for establishing maternal-fetal circulation and allowing exchange of nutrients, gases and waste products across the placental barrier.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Trophoblastic lacunae are maternal blood-filled spaces that develop in the syncytiotrophoblast during early placental development.","Trophoblastic lacunae form the precursor to the intervillous space of the mature placenta.","The syncytiotrophoblast is the outer multinucleated layer of the early placenta that invades maternal tissue."],"references":["Gaillard R, Steegers EA, de Jongste JC, Hofman A, Jaddoe VW. Tracking of fetal growth characteristics during different trimesters and the risks of adverse birth outcomes. Int J Epidemiol. 2014 Aug;43(4):1140-53. doi: 10.1093/ije/dyu036. Epub 2014 Mar 5. PMID: 24603318; PMCID: PMC4258770","Chen X, Liu H, Li Y, Zhang W, Zhou A, Xia W, Xu S. First-trimester fetal size, accelerated growth in utero, and child neurodevelopment in a cohort study. BMC Med. 2024 Apr 29;22(1):181. doi: 10.1186/s12916-024-03390-3. PMID: 38685041; PMCID: PMC11059611","Godfrey KM, Inskip HM, Hanson MA. The long-term effects of prenatal development on growth and metabolism. Semin Reprod Med. 2011 May;29(3):257-65. doi: 10.1055/s-0031-1275518. Epub 2011 Jul 18. PMID: 21769765; PMCID: PMC3685133","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58928"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15984"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58928","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58928"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-23T21:11:58+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-23T21:12:49+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8675"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73459"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"head